</treatmentCitation>
. 
<typeStatus id="B5093E88FFC2085FFE30FD1D8DF98BB6" box="[455,505,655,676]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="ADB2FBA9FFC2085FFDB9FD1C8FA08BB6" authority="Bhatti 1967" authorityName="Bhatti" authorityYear="1967" box="[590,928,654,676]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Sericothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFDB9FD1C8F218BB6" box="[590,801,654,676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Sericothrips minutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E23FDDBFFC2085FFCD0FD1C8FA08BB6" author="Bhatti, J. S." box="[807,928,654,676]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref6997" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (1967) Thysanoptera nova Indica. Published by the author, Delhi, pp. 1 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1967">Bhatti 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A0D802AFFC2085FFF60FD438E9F8A44" blockId="12.[151,1437,721,1034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">
The only species in this genus shares many character states with 
<taxonomicName id="ADB2FBA9FFC2085FFC6DFD43881E8BFB" authorityName="Shull" authorityYear="1909" box="[922,1054,721,745]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFC6DFD43881E8BFB" box="[922,1054,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Scirtothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished as follows: absence of a pair of setae in front of the first ocellus (ocellar setae pair I); absence of mid-dorsal seta on antennal segment II; absence of setae on fore wing second vein; lateral position of tergal setal pair S1 that arise close to S2 and to the lateral microtrichial fields (
<figureCitation id="F2899CAFFFC2085FFDC9FCAF8E938A44" box="[574,659,829,854]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–38" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1682,1705]" captionTargetBox="[302,1284,301,1662]" captionTargetId="figure-165@11.[302,1284,301,1662]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 33–38. Biltothrips minutus Bhatti. (33) Head and pronotum; (34) Metascutum; (35) Abdominal sternites V–VII; (36) Abdominal tergites IV–IX; (37) Antenna; (38) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929917/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="22A8D3A1FFC2085FFF30FCF38DB68D18" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" type="description">
<paragraph id="6A0D802AFFC2085FFF30FCF38DB68D18" blockId="12.[151,1437,721,1034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">
The only known species in this genus was described from both sexes collected in 
<collectingRegion id="A8764EC8FFC2085FFB99FCF089008A68" box="[1134,1280,865,890]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="12A5C0BAFFC2085FFAFBFCF389468A68" box="[1292,1350,865,890]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0E23FDDBFFC2085FFAA1FCF38CD38A8C" author="Bhatti, J. S." pageId="12" pageNumber="265" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref6997" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (1967) Thysanoptera nova Indica. Published by the author, Delhi, pp. 1 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1967">Bhatti 1967</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, specimens were collected on the 
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFCF1FC1788058A8C" bold="true" box="[774,1029,901,926]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">SOCIETY ISLANDS</emphasis>
in the Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="0E23FDDBFFC2085FFAF2FC178CD38AD0" author="Hoddle, M. S. &amp; Hoddle, C. D. &amp; Mound, L. A." pageId="12" pageNumber="265" pagination="509 - 515" refId="ref7178" refString="Hoddle, M. S., Hoddle, C. D. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2008) An inventory of Thysanoptera collected from French Polynesia. Pacific Science, 62, 509 - 515. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2984 / 1534 - 6188 (2008) 62 [509: iotcff] 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2008">
Hoddle 
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFA95FC1489958A8F" box="[1378,1429,901,925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<specimenCount id="7CB44BA3FFC2085FFF10FC388D648AD0" box="[231,356,937,962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingRegion id="A8764EC8FFC2085FFE5DFC3B8E128AD0" box="[426,530,937,962]" country="Thailand" name="Krung Thep Mahanakhon" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Bangkok</collectingRegion>
, 
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFDE9FC3B8EB58AD0" bold="true" box="[542,693,937,962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">
<collectingCountry id="12A5C0BAFFC2085FFDE9FC3B8EB58AD0" box="[542,693,937,962]" name="Thailand" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">THAILAND</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, is available in ANIC, Canberra, and the species is here recorded from 
<emphasis id="58C65C38FFC2085FFF22FC5F8D6B8AF4" bold="true" box="[213,363,973,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">
<collectingCountry id="12A5C0BAFFC2085FFF22FC5F8D6B8AF4" box="[213,363,973,998]" name="Malaysia" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">MALAYSIA</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A8764EC8FFC2085FFE8CFC5F8DD08AF4" box="[379,464,973,998]" country="Malaysia" name="Pahang" pageId="12" pageNumber="265">Pahang</collectingRegion>
, Pulau Tioman, 
<specimenCount id="7CB44BA3FFC2085FFD7DFC5F8EF78AF4" box="[650,759,973,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" type="female">4 females</specimenCount>
<specimenCount id="7CB44BA3FFC2085FFCF7FC5F8F578AF4" box="[768,855,973,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" type="male">3 males</specimenCount>
collected on Cassava leaves, 
<date id="1E0CA6EAFFC2085FFB5CFC5F891D8AF4" box="[1195,1309,973,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="265" value="2013-07-08">8.vii.2013</date>
(Ng, Y.F.), (in CISUKM and ANIC).
</paragraph>
